transcript.text: Hello and welcome to on Print Shop.
In today's video, we're excited to introduce you to our new product type, the Pattern Creator.
This feature allows customers to create custom patterns by uploading images for products such as curtains, bed sheets, food wrapping paper, gift wrapping paper, Wallpapers and more.
Once the pattern is designed, customers can easily proceed with order placement.
Let's start by exploring how pattern products can be customized and ordered at the front store.
For this demonstration, we'll use custom food wrap paper as an example.
Customers can begin by selecting product options as they would for any print product, then move to the Personalized Design tab in the Price calculator.
Pattern products now feature a colour option with four settings.
None.
One colour image, one colour background and two colours image and background.
With the none option, the uploaded image is used as is without the ability to change colours.

Once an image is uploaded, customers can access various pattern creation options including full drop, default, half drop, mirror or normal where a single image is centred and stretched across the width.
Additionally, customers can make adjustments to refine their design.

These include image scaling to modify design size, position adjustments to shift the image to top, bottom, right or left, rotation in 30°, increments left or right, and horizontal and vertical spacing for precise layout control.
After creating the pattern, customers can preview it in 2D or 3D based on models assigned in the Real preview section.
For the One Colour image option, the image loads in black by default and customers can select a custom colour from the colour box.
The real time preview will update in the image gallery.
For two colours, image and background, 2 colour boxes are available, one to modify the image colour and another for the background.
This allows customers to fully customize their designs before finale izing.
Once the pattern is ready, customers can proceed to check out.
Next, let's move to the Admin panel to see how pattern products are added.
Please note the Attern Creator is an addon feature.
Once enabled with assistance from our technical team, you will find the pattern option in the Product Type dropdown.
Setting U Attern Roducts follows the same steps as standard product's with the addition of selecting Pattern as the product type.
In the Options tab.
An additional colour selection option is available for better visualisation.
Attributes in the Studio Events tab are linked to respective pattern colour events for a seamless experience.
With Pattern Creator you can offer your customers a new level of customisation, making their designs unique and tailored to their needs.
Thank you for watching and we look forward to seeing how these updates help enhance your business operations.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
